    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>The function <strong>usort</strong> returns "true" on success. So, good news :).</p>

<p>If you want to check if the sort is done, you only have to check your $all_studies object after the usort.</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-variable">$status</span> = <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$all_studies</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"sort_objects_by_graduationyear"</span>);
<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">print_r</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$all_studies</span>);
</code></pre>
    </div>
